You Might Not Need Gatsby 你可能不需要盖茨比

May 17, 2020 2020 年 5 月 17 日

First of all, disclaimer: I love Gatbsy. This framework has entirely changed the way I think about both Static Site Generators(SSG) and React. It has sent shockwaves through the frontend community, and showed us the true potential of the so-called “JAMstack”. This website is even built with Gatsby!
首先，免责声明：我爱 Gatbsy。这个框架完全改变了我对静态站点生成器 (SSG) 和 React 的看法。它在前端社区引起了轰动，向我们展示了所谓的“JAMstack”的真正潜力。这个网站甚至是用 Gatsby 构建的！

Okay, done with disclaimer, time to complain. Let’s check out some serious issues with Gatsby, the new popular kid in React, Frontend, and SSG worlds.
好了，免责声明结束了，是时候抱怨了。让我们来看看 Gatsby 的一些严重问题，它是 React、Frontend 和 SSG 世界中的新宠。

What could possibly be wrong with Gatsby?
盖茨比可能有什么问题？

In short bullet point format: 简而言之，要点格式：

  • Why do I have to write a GraphQL query to render an image?
    为什么我必须编写 GraphQL 查询来渲染图像？
  • Loss of some SPA/History API features, such as embedded routes. Gatsby is closer in design to traditional SSG, and kind of locked to 1 component <-> 1 URL route.
    一些 SPA/History API 功能的丢失，例如嵌入式路由。 Gatsby 在设计上更接近于传统的 SSG，并且有点锁定到 1 个组件 <-> 1 个 URL 路由。
  • Sharp dependency is huge and always breaks
    尖锐的依赖性是巨大的并且总是会中断
  • Opinionated plugin ecosystem — unnecessary wrapper/obfuscation of existing APIs. For example, I can’t just use styled-components, I have to use gatsby-plugin-styled-components.
    自以为是的插件生态系统——对现有 API 进行不必要的包装/混淆。例如，我不能只使用 styled-components ，我必须使用 gatsby-plugin-styled-components 。
  • Architecture, code splitting, etc. for the most part have to be done “the Gatsby way”.
    架构、代码拆分等大部分都必须以“Gatsby 方式”完成。

Note: As a reminder, the goal in using a SSG like Gatsby is to create fast, static, SEO-friendly pages. That’s a gross oversimplification, yes. But basically: we want to send meaningful HTML content over the line when users visit our site, rather than just sending the <div id="app"></div>.
注意：提醒一下，使用像 Gatsby 这样的 SSG 的目的是创建快速、静态、SEO 友好的页面。这是一个严重的过度简化，是的。但基本上：我们希望在用户访问我们的网站时通过线路发送有意义的 HTML 内容，而不是仅仅发送 <div id="app"></div> 。

If not Gatsby…then how? 如果不是盖茨比……那又如何呢？

So — are the above headaches a price worth paying for creating static pages with React?
那么——上述令人头疼的问题值得为使用 React 创建静态页面付出代价吗？

For small projects, Gatsby is probably not worth the headaches. Can’t I just write Plain Old React without having to conform to “the Gatsby way”? And get a static site out of it? How?
对于小型项目，Gatsby 可能不值得为之头疼。我不能只写 Plain Old React 而不必遵循“Gatsby 方式”吗？并从中获取静态站点？如何？

Static Generation

The answer is prerendering. 答案是预渲染。

Once again, I went down the prerendering rabbit hole, my old nemesis. I think of prerendering as a life hack — turn your client rendered app into a static site, for free. Again, gross oversimplification.
我又一次进入了预渲染的兔子洞，我的老对手。我认为预渲染是一种生活窍门——免费将您的客户端渲染应用程序变成静态站点。再次，严重过度简化。

This time, I came back from the rabbit hole with react-snap. In my experience, this library works a lot better than the popular prerender-spa-plugin. It also doesn’t rely on Webpack, and supports inline critical css!
这一次，我带着 react-snap 从兔子洞里回来了。根据我的经验，这个库比流行的 prerender-spa-plugin 工作得更好。它也不依赖于 Webpack，并且支持内联关键 css！

Offline Support

Do you really need gatsby-plugin-offline to make your site work offline? Instead of learning it “the Gatsby way”, you can instead spend that cognitive investment on the vanilla Service Worker API, and get something more configurable. You also get universally applicable knowledge this way, not Gatsby specific knowledge.
您真的需要 gatsby-plugin-offline 来让您的站点离线工作吗？与其以“Gatsby 方式”学习它，不如将认知投资花在 vanilla Service Worker API 上，并获得更可配置的东西。您还可以通过这种方式获得普遍适用的知识，而不是 Gatsby 特定知识。

The configuration and usage is equally complex as setting up offline support for Gatsby, in my experience. Check the MDN Docs on Service Worker API.
根据我的经验，配置和使用与为 Gatsby 设置离线支持一样复杂。检查 Service Worker API 上的 MDN 文档。

Show me code 显示代码

If you want to try this vanilla-static-react setup, you can try my scaffolding tool directly.
如果你想尝试这个 vanilla-static-react 设置，你可以直接尝试我的脚手架工具。

$ npx sssrpbp --name=some-project

Also, this all works for Preact just the same.
此外，这一切都适用于 Preact。

$ npx sssrpbp --name=some-micro-project --template=preact

This will create a react app set up to use react-snap and parcel, with my personal picks for prettier and eslint setup. It’s probably more of a personal preference tool here, not a “framework”. Regardless, the key ingredients are there and could be a starting point.
这将创建一个 React 应用程序，设置为使用 react-snap 和 parcel，以及我个人选择的 prettier 和 eslint 设置。它在这里可能更像是一种个人偏好工具，而不是“框架”。无论如何，关键成分都在那里，可以作为一个起点。

Some more code links where I’m using this alternative to Gatsby:
我在其中使用此替代 Gatsby 的更多代码链接：

  • sssrpbp — the above mentioned scaffolding tool/boilerplate.
    sssrpbp — 上面提到的脚手架工具/样板。
  • pprmnt — an app built using this setup, including offline support.
    pprmnt — 使用此设置构建的应用程序，包括离线支持。
  • damachabeats — another app using this setup.
    damachabeats——另一个使用此设置的应用程序。

Conclusion

These are just my personal ramblings on the topic of static React, and I found what I like the best and what I’m most productive with. There’s also react-static, which takes a similar (but slightly stripped down) approach as Gatsby.
这些只是我对静态 React 主题的个人漫谈，我发现了我最喜欢的东西和我最有效率的东西。还有 react-static ，它采用与 Gatsby 类似（但稍微精简）的方法。

No other comments on this topic.
没有关于此主题的其他评论。

关键视觉：前几天晚上我骑自行车拍的照片。与 React 完全无关。
